==English==

===Etymology===
[[onomatopoeic]]

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|bēp}}, {{IPA|/biːp/}}, {{SAMPA|/bi:p/}}
*: [[Rhymes:English:-iːp|Rhymes: -iːp]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# The sound produced by the [[horn]] of a [[car]], or any similar sound.
# A short, [[electronically]] produced [[tone]].
# A word used to substitute for a curse word in everyday conversation.

====Synonyms====
*(''electronically produced''): [[bleep]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# {{transitive}} To sound (something that makes a beep).
#: ''The motorists in the traffic jam were getting more and more frustrated and started '''beeping''' their horns.''
# {{transitive}} To have intercourse
#: ''Jason '''beeped''' with Sharlene after they had drank a few beers.
# {{intransitive}} To produce a beep.

====Synonyms====
*(''sound (a car horn)''): [[honk]], [[hoot]], [[sound]], [[toot]]
*[[intercourse]], [[sex]], [[fuck]]

